---
import Heading from "@components/Heading.astro";
import HeadingLarge from "@components/HeadingLarge.astro";
import Text from "@components/Text.astro";
import View from "@components/View.astro";
import Group from "@components/Group.astro";
import { Layout } from "@layouts";
import Image from "@components/Image.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="Origami | Jonathon Toon | Software Designer, Product Leader"
  description="Jonathon Toon is a versatile software designer and product leader based in Aotearoa New Zealand."
  keywords="design, software, product, fractional, leadership, new zealand, aotearoa, technology, typescript, start ups, engineering, mentorship, coaching, adplist"
  twitterHandle="@jonathontoon"
  canonicalUrl="https://www.jonathontoon.com/"
  ogImage="/images/og-image.png"
>
  <Group>
    <HeadingLarge class="px-2">Origami</HeadingLarge>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Founded in 2012 as a mobile ecommerce platform, Origami pivoted after a
      modest raise to focus on mobile payments in Japan's cash-dominant market
      and in a pre-Apple Pay world.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      I joined as a designer when I moved to Japan in 2015, expanding the design
      team to three people and working on some minor feature updates before
      moving into prototyping new payment experiences.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Working in a culture I had little understanding of at the time was
      incredibly formative. It taught me that what feels intuitive to users
      varies dramatically by context. Assumptions about "good design" often don't
      translate across cultures, making local user research and cultural
      awareness essential.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <View class="px-2">
      <View class="h-px w-full bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-700" />
    </View>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Origami Pay</Heading>
    <Text class="px-2">
      One of the company's moonshots. A novel payment method using Bluetooth
      technology that would let customers pay before Apple Pay was widely
      supported in Japan. I worked closely with an iOS engineer to prototype the
      experience directly in code, focusing on making purchases feel enjoyable
      and effortless.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      Before we shipped, I added a feature to let customers rate their in-store
      experience. This idea which was really just an afterthought became a big
      value add for store owners. They finally had insights beyond purchase
      history, to understand how customers actually felt about shopping in their
      stores. Something traditional payment methods didn't provide.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/origami-pay.png"
      alt="Mobile payment flow optimized for Japanese market preferences."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
    <Image
      src="/images/work/origami-ipad-payment.png"
      alt="Mobile payment flow optimized for Japanese market preferences."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Heading class="px-2">Core Navigation</Heading>
    <Text class="px-2">
      With promotions for Origami regularly happening in malls and shopping
      centers, we needed to let people browse and pay without creating accounts
      first.
    </Text>
    <Text class="px-2">
      To support this need I redesigned core call to actions to prioritize
      payment functions (paying, cards, receipts) as the most prominent
      features, while moving the original ecommerce view to a secondary tab.
    </Text>
  </Group>
  <Group>
    <Image
      src="/images/work/origami-navigation.png"
      alt="Navigation system designed for single-handed mobile usage patterns."
      class="w-full rounded-xl bg-stone-200 dark:bg-stone-800"
      lightbox={true}
    />
  </Group>
</Layout>
